Global Trusted Platform Module Chips Market Insights
Trusted Platform Module Chips Market size was valued at USD 1.35 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 4.53 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 17.66% from 2024 to 2030.

Trusted Platform Module Chips Market Overview
The global Trusted Platform Module (TPM) Chips market is experiencing significant growth. In 2023, the market was valued at approximately USD 89 million and is projected to reach USD 291.5 million by 2030, reflecting a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 18.5% during this period. This growth is driven by increasing concerns over data security and the rising adoption of digital transformation initiatives across various industries. The market is characterized by the presence of key players such as Infineon Technologies, Intel, and NXP Semiconductors, who are actively contributing to the development and integration of TPM solutions.

